:\"**Examining unmarshalling permissions**\\n\\nI'm considering how TypePermission defines the object type being unmarshalled, which for a Class object is java.lang.Class, not Inventory. I think the string name might work. The payload reading uses the configured XStream security rather than the permissions parameter, which seems good. Should I consider using AnyTypePermission? But I want to avoid anything too broad. There’s a lot here to think about as I weigh my options carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java Object Streaming**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the possibility of using Java's ObjectOutputStream in combination with AnnotationMapper, though it seems challenging. XStream might provide a custom ObjectOutputStream through methods like xstream.createObjectOutputStream and writing to xstream.getMapper. I wonder if making getMapper public could help, as it returns AnnotationMapper. Also, there could be implications when writing the Mapper. It might be worth checking the current git status before making any edits. Let's figure this out!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Ak3u9pMJM51tQ3XAQBgSAFJh|fc_089725bf52d4e2f70169f00e90cf5481a3b84dfa0c67982c53", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 829, "output": 812, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32361, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777340034465, "responseId": "resp_089725bf52d4e2f70169f00e82f51081a3baf71cf41403fdf8"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Ak3u9pMJM51tQ3XAQBgSAFJh|fc_089725bf52d4e2f70169f00e90cf5481a3b84dfa0c67982c53", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "?? metadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777340049134}]}
